{"id":"e4c844830a8acd237f9c78e6c8a55badac555fb7","axis":"silent","repo":"sveltejs/kit","sha":"e4c844830a8acd237f9c78e6c8a55badac555fb7","parsed":{"files":[{"path":".changeset/breaking-remove-query-run.md","lines":["@@ -0,0 +1,5 @@","+---","+'@sveltejs/kit': minor","+---","+","+breaking: the `.run()` method has been removed from remote queries on both the client and the server. Use `await query()` directly instead — it now works everywhere"],"additions":5,"deletions":0,"truncated":false},{"path":".changeset/feat-isomorphic-query-await.md","lines":["@@ -0,0 +1,5 @@","+---","+'@sveltejs/kit': minor","+---","+","+feat: remote queries can now be awaited in any context (event handlers, module scope, async callbacks), not just inside reactive contexts. The cache is shared across reactive and non-reactive subscribers, so awaiting a query in an event handler will dedupe with components that have already subscribed to the same query."],"additions":5,"deletions":0,"truncated":false},{"path":"documentation/docs/20-core-concepts/60-remote-functions.md","lines":["@@ -166,48 +166,25 @@ Both the argument and the return value are serialized with [devalue](https://git"," "," When you call a query function, SvelteKit serializes the argument you call it with and uses it as a cache key. On the server, this is used to create a request-scoped cache so that multiple invocations of the same query only result in the work happening once. On the client, SvelteKit does something similar: Multiple identical invocations of a query all point to the same instance."," ","-To prevent memory leaks, this instance is kept cached only as long as it is actively used on the page in a _reactive context_, which means it must be created in a [derived](../svelte/$derived), [effect](../svelte/$effect) or component template. In practice, you're most likely to run into this limitation in universal `load` functions, event handlers, or when trying to access a query's data during module initialization.","-","-To illustrate:","+You can `await` a query in any context — components, event handlers, universal `load` functions, async callbacks — and SvelteKit will dedupe with whatever other consumers are using the same query. For example:"," "," ```svelte"," <script>"," \timport { getData } from './data.remote.js';"," ","-\t// this instance is \"anchored\" to the reactive context of this component","-\tconst data = getData();","+  // awaited inside the component template — populates the cache","+  const data = getData();"," </script>"," ","-<!--","-\tAwaiting `data` in a non-reactive context is valid, because it's anchored","-\tand will be cleaned up when this component is cleaned up.","-<button onclick={async () => console.log(await data)}>","-\tclick me!","-</button>","+<p>{await data}</p>"," ","-<!--","-\tThis, however, will throw, because `getData` isn't anchored to any reactive context.","+<!-- this dedupes with the component-level use above; no extra request -->"," <button onclick={async () => console.log(await getData())}>","-\tdon't click me!","-</button>","-```","-","-This limitation only applies to accessing the _data_ of a query by `await`ing it or trying to access its properties. If all you need is one-off access to the query's data, you can call `query.run`:","-","-```svelte","-<script>","-  import { getData } from './data.remote.js';","-</script>","-","-<!-- This bypasses the cache and runs the query directly, returning a plain old Promise<T> -->","-<button onclick={async () => console.log(await getData().run())}>"," \tclick me!"," </button>"," ```"," ","-You can also still call [`refresh`](#query-Refreshing-queries) and `set` in non-reactive contexts. If there are no active listeners to the query, they both result in no-ops.","+The cache is shared as long as the query is in active use — rendered in a component, currently being awaited, or otherwise referenced. Once nothing is using it, the cached value is released."," "," ### Refreshing queries"," ","@@ -311,7 +288,7 @@ If the connection drops, `connected` becomes `false`. SvelteKit will attempt to"," "," Unlike `query`, live queries do not have a `refresh()` method, as they are self-updating."," ","-As with `query` and `query.batch`, call `.run()` outside render when you need imperative access. For live queries, `run()` returns a `Promise<AsyncGenerator<T>>`.","+If you need direct, imperative access to the underlying stream of values (rather than the reactive `current` property), live queries expose a `.run()` method that returns an `AsyncGenerator<T>`. This can only be called outside render — in event handlers, `load` functions, and so on."," "," > [!NOTE] It's essential that you don't cache live query responses in a service worker, since the cloned response will continue streaming long after the page is closed. Make sure that your caching logic excludes any responses with a `Cache-Control` header that includes `no-store`."," "],"additions":7,"deletions":28,"truncated":false},{"path":"packages/kit/kit.vitest.config.js","lines":["@@ -1,8 +1,20 @@"," import { fileURLToPath } from 'node:url';","+import { svelte } from '@sveltejs/vite-plugin-svelte';"," import { defineConfig } from 'vitest/config';"," "," // this file needs a custom name so that the numerous test subprojects don't all pick it up","+/** @param {string} specifier */","+const mock = (specifier) => fileURLToPath(new URL(`./test/mocks/${specifier}.js`, import.meta.url));","+","+const exclude = [","+\t'**/node_modules/**',","+\t'**/.svelte-kit/**',","+\t'**/.{idea,git,cache,output,temp}/**',","+\t'**/{karma,rollup,webpack,vite,vitest,jest,ava,babel,nyc,cypress,tsup,build}.config.*'","+];","+"," export default defineConfig({","+\tplugins: [svelte({ compilerOptions: { hmr: false, experimental: { async: true } } })],"," \tdefine: {"," \t\t__SVELTEKIT_SERVER_TRACING_ENABLED__: false"," \t},","@@ -13,16 +25,37 @@ export default defineConfig({"," \t},"," \ttest: {"," \t\talias: {","-\t\t\t'__sveltekit/paths': fileURLToPath(new URL('./test/mocks/path.js', import.meta.url))","+\t\t\t// Order matters: vite prefix-matches with trailing-slash, so longer keys must","+\t\t\t// come first to avoid `$app/paths` matching `$app/paths/internal/client`.","+\t\t\t'$app/paths/internal/client': mock('app-paths-internal-client'),","+\t\t\t'$app/paths/internal/server': mock('app-paths-internal-server'),","+\t\t\t'$app/paths': mock('app-paths'),","+\t\t\t'__sveltekit/environment': mock('sveltekit-environment'),","+\t\t\t'__sveltekit/paths': mock('sveltekit-paths')"," \t\t},","-\t\tpool: 'threads',","-\t\tmaxWorkers: 1,","-\t\tinclude: ['src/**/*.spec.js'],","-\t\texclude: [","-\t\t\t'**/node_modules/**',","-\t\t\t'**/.svelte-kit/**',","-\t\t\t'**/.{idea,git,cache,output,temp}/**',","-\t\t\t'**/{karma,rollup,webpack,vite,vitest,jest,ava,babel,nyc,cypress,tsup,build}.config.*'","+\t\tprojects: [","+\t\t\t{","+\t\t\t\textends: true,","+\t\t\t\ttest: {","+\t\t\t\t\tname: 'server',","+\t\t\t\t\tenvironment: 'node',","+\t\t\t\t\tinclude: ['src/**/*.spec.js'],","+\t\t\t\t\texclude: [...exclude, 'src/**/*.svelte.spec.js']","+\t\t\t\t}","+\t\t\t},","+\t\t\t{","+\t\t\t\textends: true,","+\t\t\t\ttest: {","+\t\t\t\t\tname: 'client',","+\t\t\t\t\tenvironment: 'jsdom',","+\t\t\t\t\tinclude: ['src/**/*.svelte.spec.js'],","+\t\t\t\t\texclude,","+\t\t\t\t\t// `forks` (child_process) accepts `--expose-gc`; `threads` (worker_threads) does not.","+\t\t\t\t\tpool: 'forks',","+\t\t\t\t\tmaxWorkers: 1,","+\t\t\t\t\texecArgv: ['--expose-gc']","+\t\t\t\t}","+\t\t\t}"," \t\t]"," \t}"," });"],"additions":42,"deletions":9,"truncated":false},{"path":"packages/kit/package.json","lines":["@@ -19,9 +19,9 @@"," \t\"type\": \"module\","," \t\"dependencies\": {"," \t\t\"@standard-schema/spec\": \"^1.0.0\",","-\t\t\"@sveltejs/acorn-typescript\": \"^1.0.5\",","+\t\t\"@sveltejs/acorn-typescript\": \"^1.0.9\","," \t\t\"@types/cookie\": \"^0.6.0\",","-\t\t\"acorn\": \"^8.14.1\",","+\t\t\"acorn\": \"^8.16.0\","," \t\t\"cookie\": \"^0.6.0\","," \t\t\"devalue\": \"^5.8.1\","," \t\t\"esm-env\": \"^1.2.2\",","@@ -39,6 +39,7 @@"," \t\t\"@types/node\": \"catalog:\","," \t\t\"@types/set-cookie-parser\": \"catalog:\","," \t\t\"dts-buddy\": \"^0.8.0\",","+\t\t\"jsdom\": \"catalog:\","," \t\t\"rollup\": \"^4.59.0\","," \t\t\"svelte\": \"catalog:\","," \t\t\"typescript\": \"^5.3.3\",","@@ -46,8 +47,8 @@"," \t\t\"vitest\": \"catalog:\""," \t},"," \t\"peerDependencies\": {","-\t\t\"@sveltejs/vite-plugin-svelte\": \"^3.0.0 || ^4.0.0-next.1 || ^5.0.0 || ^6.0.0-next.0 || ^7.0.0\","," \t\t\"@opentelemetry/api\": \"^1.0.0\",","+\t\t\"@sveltejs/vite-plugin-svelte\": \"^3.0.0 || ^4.0.0-next.1 || ^5.0.0 || ^6.0.0-next.0 || ^7.0.0\","," \t\t\"svelte\": \"^4.0.0 || ^5.0.0-next.0\","," \t\t\"typescript\": \"^5.3.3 || ^6.0.0\","," \t\t\"vite\": \"^5.0.3 || ^6.0.0 || ^7.0.0-beta.0 || ^8.0.0\""],"additions":4,"deletions":3,"truncated":false},{"path":"packages/kit/src/exports/public.d.ts","lines":["@@ -2232,12 +2232,6 @@ export type RemoteResource<T> = Promise<T> & {"," \t);"," "," export type RemoteQuery<T> = RemoteResource<T> & {","-\t/**","-\t * Returns a plain promise with the result.","-\t * Unlike awaiting the resource directly, this can only be used _outside_ render","-\t * (i.e. in load functions, event handlers and so on)","-\t */","-\trun(): Promise<T>;"," \t/**"," \t * On the client, this function will update the value of the query without re-fetching it."," \t *"],"additions":0,"deletions":6,"truncated":false},{"path":"packages/kit/src/runtime/app/server/remote/query.js","lines":["@@ -448,21 +448,17 @@ function create_query_resource(__, payload, state, fn) {"," \t\t\tconst value = is_immediate_refresh ? get_promise() : fn();"," \t\t\treturn update_refresh_value(refresh_context, value, is_immediate_refresh);"," \t\t},","-\t\trun() {","-\t\t\t// potential TODO: if we want to be able to run queries at the top level of modules / outside of the request context, we could technically remove","-\t\t\t// the requirement that `state` is defined, but that's kind of an annoying change to make, so we're going to wait on that until we have any sort of","-\t\t\t// concrete use case.","-\t\t\tif (!state.is_in_universal_load) {","-\t\t\t\tthrow new Error(","-\t\t\t\t\t'On the server, .run() can only be called in universal `load` functions. Anywhere else, just await the query directly'","-\t\t\t\t);","-\t\t\t}","-\t\t\treturn get_response(__, payload, state, fn);","-\t\t},"," \t\t/** @param {any} value */"," \t\tset(value) {"," \t\t\treturn update_refresh_value(get_refresh_context(__, 'set', payload), value);"," \t\t},","+\t\t// TODO 3.0 remove this","+\t\t// @ts-expect-error This method no longer exists","+\t\trun() {","+\t\t\tthrow new Error(","+\t\t\t\t`\\`myQuery().run()\\` has been removed — please replace it with \\`myQuery()\\`. See https://github.com/sveltejs/kit/pull/15779 for more details`","+\t\t\t);","+\t\t},"," \t\t/** @type {Promise<any>['then']} */"," \t\tthen(onfulfilled, onrejected) {"," \t\t\treturn get_promise().then(onfulfilled, onrejected);"],"additions":7,"deletions":11,"truncated":false},{"path":"packages/kit/src/runtime/client/client.js","lines":["@@ -1,5 +1,6 @@","-/** @import { RemoteQueryCacheEntry } from './remote-functions/query.svelte.js' */","-/** @import { RemoteLiveQueryCacheEntry } from './remote-functions/query-live.svelte.js' */","+/** @import { CacheEntry } from './remote-functions/cache.svelte.js' */","+/** @import { Query } from './remote-functions/query/instance.svelte.js' */","+/** @import { LiveQuery } from './remote-functions/query-live/instance.svelte.js' */"," import { BROWSER, DEV } from 'esm-env';"," import * as svelte from 'svelte';"," import { HttpError, Redirect, SvelteKitError } from '@sveltejs/kit/internal';","@@ -302,13 +303,13 @@ const preload_tokens = new Set();"," export let pending_invalidate;"," "," /**","- * @type {Map<string, Map<string, RemoteQueryCacheEntry<any>>>}","+ * @type {Map<string, Map<string, CacheEntry<Query<any>>>>}","  * A map of query id -> payload -> query internals for all active queries.","  */"," export const query_map = new Map();"," "," /**","- * @type {Map<string, Map<string, RemoteLiveQueryCacheEntry<any>>>}","+ * @type {Map<string, Map<string, CacheEntry<LiveQuery<any>>>>}","  * A map of id -> payload -> live query internals for all active queries.","  */"," export const live_query_map = new Map();"],"additions":5,"deletions":4,"truncated":false},{"path":"packages/kit/src/runtime/client/remote-functions/cache.svelte.js","lines":["@@ -0,0 +1,156 @@","+import { tick } from 'svelte';","+","+/**","+ * @template R","+ * @typedef {object} CacheEntry","+ * @property {number} proxy_count The number of live proxy instances referencing this","+ *   entry. The entry is eligible for eviction when this hits zero.","+ * @property {R} resource The actual reactive resource (Query or LiveQuery).","+ * @property {() => void} cleanup Tears down the `$effect.root` that owns the resource.","+ *   Run when the entry is evicted.","+ */","+","+/**","+ * @template R","+ * @typedef {{ entry: CacheEntry<R>, id: string, payload: string }} ProxyFinalizerToken","+ */","+","+/**","+ * Cache controller bound to a specific cache map and resource teardown function. Owns the","+ * eviction scheduling and FinalizationRegistry for its cache.","+ *","+ * Methods are defined as arrow-function class fields so they can be destructured and","+ * re-exported without losing their `this` binding.","+ *","+ * @template R","+ */","+export class CacheController {","+\t/** @type {Map<string, Map<string, CacheEntry<R>>>} */","+\t#cache_map;","+","+\t/** @type {((resource: R) => void) | undefined} */","+\t#destroy_resource;","+","+\t/**","+\t * The held value points at the cache entry the proxy is contributing to. When the","+\t * proxy is GC'd, we decrement that entry's `proxy_count` and schedule a deferred","+\t * eviction check.","+\t *","+\t * @type {FinalizationRegistry<ProxyFinalizerToken<R>>}","+\t */","+\t#proxy_finalizer = new FinalizationRegistry(({ entry, id, payload }) => {","+\t\tthis.deref(entry, id, payload);","+\t});","+","+\t/**","+\t * @param {Map<string, Map<string, CacheEntry<R>>>} cache_map","+\t * @param {(resource: R) => void} [destroy_resource] Optional teardown hook called on","+\t *   the resource itself before the cache entry's `$effect.root` cleanup runs. Used by","+\t *   live queries to detach event listeners and abort connections.","+\t */","+\tconstructor(cache_map, destroy_resource) {","+\t\tthis.#cache_map = cache_map;","+\t\tthis.#destroy_resource = destroy_resource;","+\t}","+","+\t/**","+\t * Get-or-create the cache entry for `(id, payload)`. The resource is constructed","+\t * inside an `$effect.root`, the cleanup of which is stored on the entry.","+\t *","+\t * @param {string} id","+\t * @param {string} payload","+\t * @param {() => R} create_resource","+\t * @returns {CacheEntry<R>}","+\t */","+\tensure_entry = (id, payload, create_resource) => {","+\t\tlet entries = this.#cache_map.get(id);","+","+\t\tif (!entries) {","+\t\t\tentries = new Map();","+\t\t\tthis.#cache_map.set(id, entries);","+\t\t}","+","+\t\tlet entry = entries.get(payload);","+","+\t\tif (!entry) {","+\t\t\tconst c = /** @type {CacheEntry<R>} */ ({","+\t\t\t\tproxy_count: 0,","+\t\t\t\tresource: /** @type {R} */ (/** @type {unknown} */ (null)),","+\t\t\t\tcleanup: /** @type {() => void} */ (/** @type {unknown} */ (null))","+\t\t\t});","+","+\t\t\tc.cleanup = $effect.root(() => {","+\t\t\t\tc.resource = create_resource();","+\t\t\t});","+","+\t\t\tentry = c;","+\t\t\tentries.set(payload, entry);","+\t\t}","+","+\t\treturn entry;","+\t};","+","+\t/**","+\t * Register a reference to a resource cache entry using an anchor object with the FinalizationRegistry.","+\t * When the anchor object is garbage collected, the held value's `entry.proxy_count` is decremented","+\t * and a deferred eviction check is scheduled for `(id, payload)`.","+\t *","+\t * @param {object} anchor","+\t * @param {CacheEntry<R>} entry","+\t * @param {string} id","+\t * @param {string} payload","+\t */","+\tref = (anchor, entry, id, payload) => {","+\t\tentry.proxy_count++;","+\t\tthis.#proxy_finalizer.register(anchor, { entry, id, payload });","+\t};","+","+\t/**","+\t * Manually reference this cache entry. Danger: This entry will never be cleaned up unless the returned callback is called.","+\t *","+\t * @param {CacheEntry<R>} entry","+\t * @param {string} id","+\t * @param {string} payload","+\t */","+\tmanual_ref = (entry, id, payload) => {","+\t\tentry.proxy_count++;","+\t\treturn () => this.deref(entry, id, payload);","+\t};","+","+\t/**","+\t * Dereference this cache entry. If the entry's `proxy_count` hits zero, schedule a deferred eviction check.","+\t *","+\t * @param {CacheEntry<R>} entry","+\t * @param {string} id","+\t * @param {string} payload","+\t */","+\tderef = (entry, id, payload) => {","+\t\tentry.proxy_count--;","+\t\tvoid tick().then(() => {","+\t\t\tconst entry = this.#cache_map.get(id)?.get(payload);","+\t\t\tif (!entry || entry.proxy_count > 0) return;","+\t\t\tthis.#evict(id, payload);","+\t\t});","+\t};","+","+\t/**","+\t * Tear down the cache entry for `(id, payload)` if it exists. Runs the optional","+\t * resource teardown and the entry's `$effect.root` cleanup, then removes the entry","+\t * from the cache map.","+\t *","+\t * @param {string} id","+\t * @param {string} payload","+\t */","+\t#evict = (id, payload) => {","+\t\tconst entries = this.#cache_map.get(id);","+\t\tconst entry = entries?.get(payload);","+\t\tif (!entry) return;","+","+\t\tthis.#destroy_resource?.(entry.resource);","+\t\tentry.cleanup();","+\t\tentries?.delete(payload);","+\t\tif (entries && entries.size === 0) {","+\t\t\tthis.#cache_map.delete(id);","+\t\t}","+\t};","+}"],"additions":156,"deletions":0,"truncated":false},{"path":"packages/kit/src/runtime/client/remote-functions/cache.svelte.spec.js","lines":["@@ -0,0 +1,196 @@","+import { describe, expect, test, beforeEach } from 'vitest';","+import { tick } from 'svelte';","+import { CacheController } from './cache.svelte.js';","+","+/**","+ * Run garbage collection a handful of times. V8 sometimes needs more than one pass","+ * before a recently-allocated object is reclaimed. After each pass we yield to the","+ * microtask queue so any FinalizationRegistry callbacks (which are scheduled as","+ * tasks/microtasks after a sweep) get a chance to run.","+ */","+async function run_gc() {","+\tfor (let i = 0; i < 4; i++) {","+\t\t/** @type {() => void} */ (/** @type {any} */ (globalThis).gc)();","+\t\t// FinalizationRegistry callbacks run on a separate task queue; yield twice to","+\t\t// pick up both microtasks and the next macrotask.","+\t\tawait new Promise((resolve) => setTimeout(resolve, 0));","+\t\tawait tick();","+\t}","+\t// Flush the deferred eviction (`tick().then(...)`) inside `deref`.","+\tawait tick();","+\tawait tick();","+}","+","+/**","+ * Wait for the FinalizationRegistry to observe `anchor` as unreachable and run the","+ * `deref` callback. We poll up to `timeout` ms because GC scheduling is non-deterministic.","+ *","+ * @param {() => boolean} predicate","+ * @param {number} [timeout]","+ */","+async function wait_for(predicate, timeout = 2000) {","+\tconst start = Date.now();","+\twhile (Date.now() - start < timeout) {","+\t\tawait run_gc();","+\t\tif (predicate()) return;","+\t}","+\tthrow new Error('Timed out waiting for predicate');","+}","+","+describe('CacheController', () => {","+\t/** @type {Map<string, Map<string, import('./cache.svelte.js').CacheEntry<{ id: string, destroyed: boolean }>>>} */","+\tlet cache_map;","+\t/** @type {Array<{ id: string, destroyed: boolean }>} */","+\tlet destroyed;","+\t/** @type {CacheController<{ id: string, destroyed: boolean }>} */","+\tlet cache;","+","+\tbeforeEach(() => {","+\t\tcache_map = new Map();","+\t\tdestroyed = [];","+\t\tcache = new CacheController(cache_map, (resource) => {","+\t\t\tresource.destroyed = true;","+\t\t\tdestroyed.push(resource);","+\t\t});","+\t});","+","+\ttest('ensure_entry creates a single entry per (id, payload)', () => {","+\t\tlet constructions = 0;","+\t\tconst factory = () => {","+\t\t\tconstructions++;","+\t\t\treturn { id: 'x', destroyed: false };","+\t\t};","+","+\t\tconst a = cache.ensure_entry('q', 'p', factory);","+\t\tconst b = cache.ensure_entry('q', 'p', factory);","+\t\tconst c = cache.ensure_entry('q', 'other', factory);","+","+\t\texpect(constructions).toBe(2);","+\t\texpect(a).toBe(b);","+\t\texpect(a).not.toBe(c);","+\t\texpect(cache_map.get('q')?.size).toBe(2);","+\t});","+","+\ttest('ref increments proxy_count', () => {","+\t\tconst entry = cache.ensure_entry('q', 'p', () => ({ id: 'x', destroyed: false }));","+\t\texpect(entry.proxy_count).toBe(0);","+","+\t\tconst anchor = {};","+\t\tcache.ref(anchor, entry, 'q', 'p');","+","+\t\texpect(entry.proxy_count).toBe(1);","+\t});","+","+\ttest('manual_ref increments and the returned deref decrements proxy_count', async () => {","+\t\tconst entry = cache.ensure_entry('q', 'p', () => ({ id: 'x', destroyed: false }));","+\t\tconst release = cache.manual_ref(entry, 'q', 'p');","+\t\texpect(entry.proxy_count).toBe(1);","+","+\t\trelease();","+\t\texpect(entry.proxy_count).toBe(0);","+","+\t\t// Eviction is deferred via tick().then(...); pump microtasks","+\t\tawait tick();","+\t\tawait tick();","+","+\t\texpect(cache_map.get('q')?.get('p')).toBeUndefined();","+\t\texpect(destroyed).toHaveLength(1);","+\t});","+","+\ttest('eviction calls destroy_resource and the $effect.root cleanup', async () => {","+\t\tconst entry = cache.ensure_entry('q', 'p', () => ({ id: 'x', destroyed: false }));","+\t\tconst release = cache.manual_ref(entry, 'q', 'p');","+","+\t\trelease();","+\t\tawait tick();","+\t\tawait tick();","+","+\t\texpect(entry.resource.destroyed).toBe(true);","+\t\texpect(cache_map.has('q')).toBe(false);","+\t});","+","+\ttest('entry survives while at least one ref is alive', async () => {","